<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Continuance" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Continuance,</orth> 1) duration: <emph>c. tames the one</emph> (viz old woes), <bibl n="shak. luc 1097" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1097</bibl>. <cit><quote>long c. and increasing,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 107</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a bawd of eleven years' c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.208" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 208</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.125" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 125</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.7.14" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 7, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.3.105" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 3, 105</bibl>.<lb />2) permanence: <cit><quote>this maid hath yet in her the c. of her first affection,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.249" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 1, 249</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.4.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 4, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 1.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I Chor.</bibl>
<lb />3) abode, residence: <cit><quote>cloyed with long c. in a settled place,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.5.106" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 5, 106</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>